article.headline: Hofstra 77, William & Mary 69
article.story: HEMPSTEAD, N.Y. (AP) -- Antoine Agudio scored 29 points, including the go-ahead three-point play, as Hofstra closed with a 9-0 run to beat William & Mary 77-69 Saturday. Loren Stokes had 30 points and a career-high 15 rebounds for the Pride (14-5, 7-1 Colonial), who led 44-35 at halftime en route to their second straight win and eighth in nine games. Adam Payton scored 23 points and Laimis Kisielius added 15 for the Tribe (10-8, 3-5), who lost their fourth straight. Payton's 3-pointer closed an 8-3 run that tied the score at 67 with 2:33 left. Agudio's three-point play with 1:39 remaining started the game-closing run. He added a jumper and two foul shots and Stokes completed the scoring with two free throws with 34.3 seconds left.
